doc.after: "Hung Up" was a worldwide commercial success, peaking at number one in charts of 41 countries and earning a place in the 2007 Guinness Book of World Records, as the song topping the charts in most countries.[35] It also remains one of the best-selling singles of all time, with sales of over nine million copies worldwide.[36] In the United States, "Hung Up" debuted at twenty on the Billboard Hot 100 on the issue dated November 5, 2005. It became her highest opening position since "Ray of Light" entered the chart at five in 1998. The same week the song entered the Hot Digital Songs chart at number six and became the highest debuting single of the week on the Pop 100 Airplay, where it debuted at numberÂ 38.[37] On the issue dated November 21, 2005, the song reached a peak of number seven on the Billboard Hot 100, jumping from numberÂ 14 from previous week. The song became the chart's greatest digital gainer for that week and claimed the top position on the Hot Digital Songs chart.[38] It also tied Madonna with Elvis Presley for 36 top ten hits, which was subsequently broken by Madonna's 2008 song "4 Minutes", which peaked at number three on the Hot 100.[39] "Hung Up" debuted at numbersÂ 25 and 10 on the Hot Dance Club Play and Hot Dance Airplay charts respectively ultimately reaching the top of both.[40][41][42] It became the most successful dance song of the 2000s in the United States, by topping the Dance/Club Play Songs Decade-end tally.[43] The song also reached a peak of seven on the Pop 100 chart.[40] In 2008, the single was certified platinum by the Recording Industry Association of America for selling at least a million copies in paid digital downloads.[44] As of April 2010, the song has sold 1.2Â million digital units in the United States.[45]
